The paper proposes a new normalization technique for deep neural networks and evaluates its performance on various computer vision tasks such as ImageNet, COCO, CityScapes, ADE20K, MegaFace, and Kinetics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the end-to-end learning process of the proposed technique, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of different tasks and datasets on the choice of normalizers, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the robustness of the proposed technique to different batch sizes, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed technique on various benchmarks, which may suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
